{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"An image containing explicit content is flagged and held for review, not published.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Failure boundary is the vision model’s real classification quality. A stubbed classifier would hide misses on explicit imagery. Rejected higher level (Workflow) because behavior text describes a single model decision path: \"An image containing explicit content is flagged...\", not a multi-agentic sequence.","test_description":"Run real image moderation calls on a labeled explicit-image set and assert each sample is flagged and routed to review-hold state, with no publish side effect.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.07,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.7,"Workflow":0.12}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"A text post containing hate speech is flagged regardless of obfuscation techniques (e.g., letter substitution, unicode lookalikes).","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This is model robustness/semantic detection quality under adversarial text variants. Deterministic mocks would always pass and miss real failures. Rejected higher level (Workflow) because behavior is one text-classification decision, not multiple agentic stages.","test_description":"Submit a curated corpus of obfuscated hate-speech variants to the real text model path and assert flag+hold outcomes across variants.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.78,"Workflow":0.12}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A post that passes both content checks is published rather than held or silently dropped.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Primary risk is module handoff/orchestration: image result + text result + decision/publish path. Behavior text explicitly conditions on passing checks (\"passes both content checks\"), so model output quality is not under test. Rejecte